<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

<div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Don't waste -ED cheaply:</span> Adding ED to PLAY for PLAYED only scores 3 extra points. Save your D for a higher-scoring independent play unless the extension crosses premium squares.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Target power-tile verbs:</span> The best -ED plays use high-value tiles: QUIZZED (35), WHIZZED (30), JINXED (21). Learn which power-tile verbs accept -ED directly.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel play potential:</span> -ED extensions create parallel two-letter words. If PLAY is on the board, adding ED below creates PE, LE, AD — each scoring independently. Check the two-letter word list first.</p>
